// File-level variables have the highest priority.
// They override any value from http-client.env.json.
@baseUrl = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com
@userId = 7

// Variables can reference earlier variables
@postsUrl = {{baseUrl}}/posts

### File-level variables in action
GET {{postsUrl}}?userId={{userId}}

### Environment variable from http-client.env.json
// "Token" is defined in the env file, not here.
// Select an environment (dev, staging, production) from the sidebar.
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/1
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}

### Shared variables apply to all environments
// "Timeout" lives under $shared so it resolves regardless of
// which environment you pick.
GET https://httpbin.org/get
X-Timeout: {{Timeout}}

### Override demonstration
// "apiBase" exists in both $shared and the environment configs.
// The environment-specific value wins over $shared.
// A file-level @variable would win over everything.
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/1
